<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFA9FFF36DC2FA68FC10AD47" pageId="13" pageNumber="1526" type="description">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFA9FFF36DC2FA68FC10AD47" blockId="13.[178,1085,1525,1605]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1526">
Diagnosis: The metatibial glandular pit is prominent in the males of 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FFA9FFF36EB8FA68FBA9AD08" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2015" box="[968,1084,1525,1546]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Artoadenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFA9FFF36EB8FA68FBA9AD08" box="[968,1084,1525,1546]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1526">Artoadenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FFA9FFF36D91F98FFEF0AD25" authorityName="CHEVROLAT. Part" authorityYear="1834" box="[225,357,1554,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Platynoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFA9FFF36D91F98FFEF0AD25" box="[225,357,1554,1575]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1526">Platynoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. But, specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FFA9FFF36F4CF98EFD13AD25" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2015" box="[572,646,1554,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Artoadenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dius">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFA9FFF36F4CF98EFD13AD25" box="[572,646,1554,1576]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1526">A. dius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have subsecuriform terminal palpomeres, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FFA9FFF36C7BF9B2FE1AAD46" authorityName="CHEVROLAT. Part" authorityYear="1834" box="[267,399,1583,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Platynoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="1555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFA9FFF36C7BF9B2FE1AAD46" box="[267,399,1583,1604]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1526">Platynoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens have securiform terminal palpomeres.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
